msIdentifier.note:
The fragment is a part from the 15th-century Russian Evangelion Aprakos (Codex F, ff. 6-7, 9-10 in Wessél 1985), represented by a few more leaves, kept in various collections (Steensland 2003): 
                        1. National Record Office, Stockholm, Stafs. IV: 10 (Fr 11391); RA, Fr 11521 (codex 1658);
                        2. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a15:A-B;
                        3. Biblioteka Adademii nauk, Sankt-Petersburg 4.9.7: 2-3, 5; 6-8;
                        4. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a10:A-B, C-D;
                        5. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a6;
                        6. The British Library, Add. 34386, f.29;
                        7. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a23;
